description Test underlining in diagnostic output.
program diagnostic-output
file file1 <>
This is line one without tabs.
	This line has a tab at the beginning.
This line has	a tab in the middle.
end-of-inline-data
stdin
read file1
notice {file1 1 1 0} start of line, zero width
notice {file1 1 1 1} start of line, width 1
notice {file1 2 1 1} just the tab
notice {file1 2 2 1} past the tab
notice {file1 1 18 7} no tabs in line
notice {file1 2 29 9} tab at beginning
notice {file1 3 28 6} tab in middle
end-of-inline-data
stderr
file1:1:1: notice: start of line, zero width
This is line one without tabs.
^
file1:1:1: notice: start of line, width 1
This is line one without tabs.
^
file1:2:1: notice: just the tab
        This line has a tab at the beginning.
^^^^^^^^
file1:2:2: notice: past the tab
        This line has a tab at the beginning.
        ^
file1:1:18: notice: no tabs in line
This is line one without tabs.
                 ^^^^^^^
file1:2:29: notice: tab at beginning
        This line has a tab at the beginning.
                                   ^^^^^^^^^
file1:3:28: notice: tab in middle
This line has   a tab in the middle.
                             ^^^^^^
end-of-inline-data
